the lens : These differences in the relative proportions of alphaA and alphaB within the lens suggest different functions for the two subunits in the developing lens.
the lens : Moreover, expression of alpha-crystallin, particularly alphaB, was shown to not be restricted to the lens.
the lens : In the lens, alpha-crystallin also associates with type III intermediate filament proteins and the beaded filament proteins CP49 and CP115, and correct beaded filament assembly has been shown depend on the presence of alpha-crystallin [16].
the lens : A nuclear role for alphaB in the lens was supported by the findings that a subset of lens epithelial cells derived from alphaB knockout mice demonstrated hyperproliferation and genomic instability [20].
the lens : This indicates that alphaA may play a greater role in maintaining the transparency of the lens then alphaB.
