alphaB : Moreover, expression of alpha-crystallin, particularly alphaB, was shown to not be restricted to the lens.
AlphaB : AlphaB was found to be expressed at significant levels in a variety of nonlenticular tissues, while alphaA has only been detected in small amounts in a few other tissues such as retina, spleen and thymus [8-12].
