These results : Conclusion  These results indicated that both alphaA- and alphaB-crystallin are necessary for proper fiber cell formation, and that the absence of alpha-crystallin can lead to cataract formation.
The results : The results indicate that alpha-crystallin is necessary for proper fiber cell formation and resulting lens transparency.
These studies : These studies strongly suggest that the hsp family of proteins has other functions in addition to protecting proteins and cells during stress.
